.TH "fc_lport_error" 9 "fc_lport_error" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_lport_error \- Handler for any errors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fc_lport_error
.BI "(struct fc_lport *lport "  ","
.BI "struct fc_frame *fp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lport" 12
The local port that the error was on
.IP "fp" 12
The error code encoded in a frame pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the error was caused by a resource allocation failure
then wait for half a second and retry, otherwise retry
after the e_d_tov time.
